HardView
December 2012
Scott Lowrey

HardView is a tool that shows you the hardware components that make up
a computer system.  You can see the system from one or more
perspectives including bus type, function, and subsystem.

For help with command line use, see 'hardview --help'.  

To see command line options, invoke 'man hardview'.

To see the User Guide, invoke 'info hardview'.

For design information, see the documents in the design directory of
the source distribution.

